semantics.tolerancepair

Class SearchTolerancePairCreator

  • Object
    • TolerancePairCreator
      • SearchTolerancePairCreator
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    SearchMinTolerancePairCreator

    public class SearchTolerancePairCreator
extends TolerancePairCreator
    Backtracking-Search approach to create tolerance-pairs. A search tree is explored to find all tolerance-pairs. This creator does not give progress information.
    Author:
    Tobias Falke

      • isPartialTolerancePair

        protected boolean isPartialTolerancePair(TolerancePair pair,
                             Set<RelationalConditional> leftConditionals)
        Checks if the conditions for a tolerance-pair are satisfied for the conditionals in the last subset. For each, it checks if there is a world in which it is verified for a constant and no other is falsified for any constant.
        Parameters:
        pair - Current partition-pair
        leftConditionals - Left conditionals
        Returns:
        true, if such a world is found for each conditional, false otherwise
